cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on the task of video semantic salient instance segmentation, which involves both computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the benefits of this task for robot navigation and self-driving cars, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes a new framework that leverages two different segmentation tasks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset for this task, which could also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
